Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Trim the @aubergine{1}, then cut into roughly 2cm pieces.

Pop the aubergine onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, sprinkle 
over the @dried oregano{1%sachet} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then 
toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

When the oven is hot, roast the aubergine on the top shelf until soft and 
golden, ~{25-30%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, drain and rinse the @butter beans{1%carton} in a #sieve{}.

Pop a large #saucepan{} on medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{}.

Once hot, add the @British smoked bacon lardons{90%g} and stir-fry until 
golden, ~{4-5%minutes}. IMPORTANT: Wash hands and utensils after handling 
raw meat. Cook it thoroughly.

Once golden, add the @tomato passata{1%carton}, butter beans, 
@sun-dried tomato paste{25%g}, @red wine stock paste{28%g}, 
@?sugar{1%tsp} and @water{100%ml}.

Stir together and bring to a boil, then reduce the heat. Leave to gently 
simmer until slightly thickened, ~{5-6%minutes}, then cover and set aside for 
later.

In the meantime, halve the @ciabatta{1}.

When the aubergine has finished roasting, pop the stew back on a medium heat.

Stir the @baby spinach{40%g} into the stew a handful at a time until wilted 
and piping hot, ~{1-2%minutes}, along with the roasted aubergine and 
@butter{20%g}.

Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{} if needed. Add a splash of 
@water{} if it's a little too thick.

If you're using the #toaster{}, toast the ciabatta in your toaster until 
golden.

If you're using the oven, pop them into the oven to warm through, 
~{2-3%minutes}.

Once toasted, drizzle over some @oil{}, then cut the ciabatta halves 
diagonally into triangles.

When everything's ready, share the stew between your #serving bowls{}.

Drizzle on the @pesto{32%g} and crumble over the 
@Greek style salad cheese{50%g}.

Serve the ciabatta triangles alongside for dipping.

Enjoy!